			<CASNumber>15096-52-3</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Cryolite is a mineral typically used in the aluminum smelting process as a flux to lower the melting point of other compounds. It is often synthetically produced for industrial use. It is characterized by its role in the Hall-Héroult process, compliance with relevant industrial standards, high quality, and specific technical specifications. Cryolite is generally used in production rather than consumed directly and is available 'at plant' for use in aluminum production facilities.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">冰晶石是一种通常用于铝冶炼过程中作为助熔剂以降低其他化合物的熔点的矿物。它通常为工业使用而合成产生。它通过其在霍尔-埃鲁过程中的作用，符合相关工业标准，高质量和具体技术规格而被特征化。冰晶石通常用于生产而不是直接消费，并在铝生产设施中可用于'工厂'。</common:generalComment>
